Required pipeline:
- use Hugging Face transformers + PyTorch only
- run on CPU only; never use CUDA or MPS
- load only real train.csv and test.csv from DATA_DIR = os.environ.get("DISASTER_AGENT_DATA_DIR", "data")
- DRY_RUN = os.environ.get("AGENT_DRY_RUN") == "1"
- WRITE_SUBMISSION = os.environ.get("AGENT_WRITE_SUBMISSION") == "1"
- FINAL_SUBMISSION = os.environ.get("AGENT_FINAL_SUBMISSION") == "1"
- TRAIN_FRACTION = float(os.environ.get("AGENT_TRAIN_FRACTION", "1.0"))
- SAMPLE_SEED = int(os.environ.get("AGENT_SAMPLE_SEED", "42"))
- fillna keyword, location, text with ""
- build one text field from keyword + " [SEP] " + text, else text
- use model_name from spec exactly
- if DRY_RUN, use head(dry_run_head)
- else if TRAIN_FRACTION < 1.0, randomly sample that fraction of train_df with random_state=SAMPLE_SEED and reset_index(drop=True)
- define stratify_labels = y if class counts allow, else None
- use one train_test_split with test_size=val_size, random_state=42, stratify=stratify_labels; val_size is fixed at 0.2 for the runner
- use AutoTokenizer + AutoModelForSequenceClassification + Trainer + TrainingArguments
- define a top-level Dataset class over tokenizer outputs
- the Dataset class must accept labels=None for test data
- Dataset.__getitem__ must include a "labels" tensor only when labels is not None
- Dataset.__getitem__ must return keys named exactly "input_ids" and "attention_mask", never "ids" or "mask"
- build train and validation datasets from the split variables, not from the full train_df
- build test_dataset from list(test_df["text"]), labels=None, tokenizer, and max_len only if WRITE_SUBMISSION is true
- tokenize with max_len from spec
- train with batch sizes, learning rate, weight decay, and num_epochs from spec
- TrainingArguments must include use_cpu=True, dataloader_pin_memory=False, save_strategy="no", logging_strategy="no", report_to="none", fp16=False, bf16=False, disable_tqdm=True
- if DRY_RUN, skip trainer.train()
- use `val_dataset` or `valid_dataset`, either name is fine
- predict validation logits with `trainer.predict(...).predictions` preferred
- if FINAL_SUBMISSION is true, after choosing the best cutoff, train a fresh final model on every labeled row currently loaded in train_df before test prediction
- predict test logits only if WRITE_SUBMISSION is true
- convert logits to probabilities with a stable numpy softmax
- create the submissions directory before writing the CSV only if WRITE_SUBMISSION is true
- choose best cutoff by looping over np.linspace(threshold_min, threshold_max, threshold_steps)
- when WRITE_SUBMISSION is true, save columns id,target to submission_path
- last line exactly:
